I just want to say thank you for this practice, especially today. I flew on short notice from my sweet small midwestern town to the NY metro area (where I grew up) yesterday to help my mom figure out care for my declining dad. I left my little old farmhouse by the creek, my autonomy, my dogs and cat, all the meadowlarks, my man, and the beautiful sunsets (I love the quirky home I have created). It was a strange day yesterday...some very kind people in the flights and airports, and some viciously unkind and even bully-ish. I think the masks make some people meaner in those big public places...has anyone else noticed that? Anyway, the night before, I had received some slightly negative feedback from my supervisor, after putting in 11 hours of work, and was discouraged. Through all this...and waking up today to face a lot of unknowns and my old low self esteem that I thought I had conquered long ago, I hear Adriene's wise words. Make space, open your heart, take your time, be in your body and pay attention to how you feel (aka: don't numb out), the body is a metaphor. Today I might be making space for something new that might not be very pleasant (seeing Dad in the nursing home for the first time, and knowing that my brilliant, funny, kind father is no longer working with a full deck...or even with a full suit), but who knows, right? Maybe a new job is in my future as well...thank you for this lesson. I feel courageous enough now to truly be open to whatever today wants to bring my way. Thank you and I love you all (especially Adriene and Benji)!! <3

I hope you all have had a wonderful start to the new year. I just want to share how incredible my time with Adriene has been in the Dedicate 30 day program.  I greatly appreciate how fresh each day is and how Adriene is always mindful to tell us ways to protect ourselves and enjoy the practice. I never thought I would be able to incorporate yoga in my daily life, but through sick days (where I'm doing a session on antibiotics at 11 0clcok at night because some days fly faster than others), sunny days (where you don't want to be in the house,) or even chores/work days, I fought hard to make this precious time a part of my day. I feel better, my body feels better. I struggled with basic poses like rag doll at first. However, I find know I can be present in the pose and not feel the stiffness or awkwardness that was tempting me to stop this journey. I wanted to share this with you all because I know I appreciate hearing how others are experiencing their journeys. Keep it up! It's so worth it! THanks Adriene for you time and dedication!

Adriene, I have to tell you... I was carrying my 40# sleeping kid up the stairs to my apartment this afternoon and felt that all too familiar twinge in my hip as I tried to compensate for his weight on the opposite side.
